verses.text: Ye \add are\add* the children of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God : ye shall not cut yourselves, nor make any baldness between your eyes for the dead.

For thou \add art\add* an holy people unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God , and the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* hath chosen thee to be a peculiar people unto himself, above all the nations that \add are\add* upon the earth. \p
¶ Thou shalt not eat any abominable thing.
These \add are\add* the beasts which ye shall eat : the ox , the sheep , and the goat ,
The hart , and the roebuck , and the fallow deer , and the wild goat , and the pygarg , and the wild ox , and the chamois.\f + \fr 14.5 \ft pygarg: or bison: Heb. dishon\f*
And every beast that parteth the hoof , and cleaveth the cleft into two claws , \add and\add* cheweth the cud among the beasts , that ye shall eat.

Nevertheless these ye shall not eat of them that chew the cud , or of them that divide the cloven hoof ; \add as\add* the camel , and the hare , and the coney : for they chew the cud , but divide not the hoof ; \add therefore\add* they \add are\add* unclean unto you.
And the swine , because it divideth the hoof , yet cheweth not the cud , it \add is\add* unclean unto you: ye shall not eat of their flesh , nor touch their dead carcase. \p
¶ These ye shall eat of all that \add are\add* in the waters : all that have fins and scales shall ye eat :
And whatsoever hath not fins and scales ye may not eat ; it \add is\add* unclean unto you. \p
¶ \add Of\add* all clean birds ye shall eat.
But these \add are they\add* of which ye shall not eat : the eagle , and the ossifrage , and the ospray ,
And the glede , and the kite , and the vulture after his kind ,
And every raven after his kind ,
And the owl , and the night hawk , and the cuckow , and the hawk after his kind ,
The little owl , and the great owl , and the swan ,
And the pelican , and the gier eagle , and the cormorant ,
And the stork , and the heron after her kind , and the lapwing , and the bat.
And every creeping thing that flieth \add is\add* unclean unto you: they shall not be eaten.
\add But of\add* all clean fowls ye may eat. \p

¶ Ye shall not eat \add of\add* any thing that dieth of itself : thou shalt give it unto the stranger that \add is\add* in thy gates , that he may eat it; or thou mayest sell it unto an alien : for thou \add art\add* an holy people unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God. Thou shalt not seethe a kid in his mother’s milk. \p
Thou shalt truly tithe all the increase of thy seed , that the field bringeth forth year by year.

And thou shalt eat before the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God , in the place which he shall choose to place his name there, the tithe of thy corn , of thy wine , and of thine oil , and the firstlings of thy herds and of thy flocks ; that thou mayest learn to fear the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God always.

And if the way be too long for thee, so that thou art not able to carry it; \add or\add* if the place be too far from thee, which the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God shall choose to set his name there, when the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God hath blessed thee:
Then shalt thou turn \add it\add* into money , and bind up the money in thine hand , and shalt go unto the place which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God shall choose :

And thou shalt bestow that money for whatsoever thy soul lusteth after , for oxen , or for sheep , or for wine , or for strong drink , or for whatsoever thy soul desireth : and thou shalt eat there before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God , and thou shalt rejoice , thou, and thine household ,\f + \fr 14.26 \ft desireth: Heb. asketh of thee\f*
And the Levite that \add is\add* within thy gates ; thou shalt not forsake him; for he hath no part nor inheritance with thee. \p
¶ At the end of three years thou shalt bring forth all the tithe of thine increase the same year , and shalt lay \add it\add* up within thy gates :

And the Levite , (because he hath no part nor inheritance with thee,) and the stranger , and the fatherless , and the widow , which \add are\add* within thy gates , shall come , and shall eat and be satisfied ; that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God may bless thee in all the work of thine hand which thou doest.
